The '''U-33 orbital loadlifter''', also known as a '''U-33 orbital space boat''', was a [[Transport/Legends|transport]] considered outdated by the time of the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]]. A number of [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] [[Pilot/Legends|pilots]], including [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]], gained experience in U-33 loadlifters during their training at the [[Imperial Academy/Legends|Imperial Academy]].

==Characteristics==
The standard U-33 was a durable, [[Lightspeed/Legends|sublightspeed]] transport used to convey personnel and equipment between orbital [[Space station/Legends|space stations]] and [[Spaceport/Legends|spaceports]] on the [[Planet/Legends|planets]] below.<ref name="CSWE">{{CSWECite|III|275|U-33}}</ref> It had inverted wings and was equipped with a four-stage primary thrust sequence. This model was known to have problems with its reservoir-locking mechanisms, which often stuck in one position and stopped the landing gear from fully extending or retracting.

==History==
Though replaced by newer models by the time of the [[New Order/Legends|New Order]], U-33s could still be found in operation on outlying worlds during the Civil War. Several orbital loadlifters were used for training purposes at the Imperial Academy.

Han Solo's training officer at the Academy taught his students how to successfully land a U-33 loadlifter during exercises. [[Alexsandr Badure]] had rigged one U-33 to all but self-destruct, and during Han's attempt, the loadlifter experienced major problems. Despite this, Han managed to bring the vessel to a perfect landing, though he scared his instructor almost to death in the process. For this amazing feat of piloting skill, Han earned the nickname 'Slick'.

